Name: MT.ADQSADAS.AVISIT
Description: Derived based on windowing algorithm described in SAP, Section 8.2

Name: MT.ADQSADAS.ADY
Description: ADY = ADT - TRTSDT + 1, if ADT>=TRTSDT. ADY = ADT - TRTSDT, if ADT<TRTSDT.

Name: MT.ADQSADAS.ADT
Description: SAS date from QS.QSDTC

Name: MT.ADQSADAS.BASE
Description: QS.QSSTRESN where QS.QSBLFL=Y (QS.VISITNUM=3)

Name: MT.ADQSADAS.CHG
Description: AVAL - BASE

Name: MT.ADQSADAS.PCHG
Description: 100* (CHG/BASE)

Name: MT.ADQSADAS.ANL01FL
Description: If multiple visits fall into the same visit window, then the one closest to the target day is chosen for analysis. These are flagged with ANL01FL="Y".

Name: MT.ADQSADAS.AWTDIFF
Description: Absolute difference between AWTARGET and ADY

Name: MT.ADSL.SITEGR1
Description: refer to SAP, Section 7.1 - if not pooled then SITEGR1=SITEID. If pooled, SITEGR1 will be 900

Name: MT.ADSL.TRTSDT
Description: SV.SVSTDTC where SV.VISITNUM=3, converted to SAS date

Name: MT.ADSL.TRTEDT
Description: The date of final dose (from the CRF) is EX.EXENDTC on the subject's last EX record. If the date of final dose is missing for the subject and the subject discontinued after visit 3, use the date of discontinuation as the date of last dose. Convert the date to a SAS date.

Name: MT.ADSL.TRTDURD
Description: TRTEDT-TRTSDT+1

Name: MT.ADSL.AVGDD
Description: CUMDOSE/TRTDURD

Name: MT.ADSL.CUMDOSE
Description: For TRT01PN=0 or 54: CUMDOSE=TRT01PN*TRTDURD. For TRT01PN=81: CUMDOSE will be based on 54 mg per day for the # of days subject was in 1st dosing interval (i.e., Date of visit 4 - TRTSTDT+1 if 1st interval completed, TRTEDT-TRTSTDT+1 if subject discontinued <= Visit 4 (Week 4) and > Visit 3 (Baseline)), 81 mg per day for the # of days subject was in 2nd dosing interval (i.e., Date of Visit 12 - Date of Visit 4 if 2nd interval completed, TRTEDT- Date of Visit 4 if subject discontinued <= Visit 12 (Week 24) and > Visit 4), and 54 mg per day for the # of days subject was in 3rd dosing interval (i.e., TRTEDT - Date of Visit 12 if subject continued after Visit 12).

Name: MT.ADSL.AGEGR1
Description: Grouping of AGE into <65, 65-80, and >80

Name: MT.ADSL.SAFFL
Description: Y if ITTFL='Y' and TRTSDT ne missing. N otherwise

Name: MT.ADSL.ITTFL
Description: Y if ARMCD ne ' '. N otherwise

Name: MT.ADSL.EFFFL
Description: Y if SAFFL='Y AND subject has at least one record in QS for ADAS-Cog with QS.VISITNUM>3 AND at least one record in QS for CIBIC+ with QS.VISITNUM>3, N otherwise

Name: MT.ADSL.COMP8FL
Description: Y if subject has a SV.VISITNUM=8 and TRTEDT>= date of visit 8, N otherwise

Name: MT.ADSL.COMP16FL
Description: Y if subject has a SV.VISITNUM=10 and TRTEDT>=date of visit 10, N otherwise

Name: MT.ADSL.COMP24FL
Description: Y if subject has a SV.VISITNUM=12 and TRTEDT>= date of visit 12 , N otherwise

Name: MT.ADSL.DISCONFL
Description: Y if EOSSTT='DISCONTINUED'. Null otherwise

Name: MT.ADSL.DSRAEFL
Description: Y if DCSREAS='Adverse Event'. Null otherwise

Name: MT.ADSL.BMIBL
Description: WEIGHTBL / ((HEIGHTBL*100)**2)

Name: MT.ADSL.BMIBLGR1
Description: BMIBLGR1=Normal if . < BMIBL <25. BMIBLGR1=Overweight if 25 <=BMIBL <30. BMIBLGR1=Obese if BMIBL >=30

Name: MT.ADSL.HEIGHTBL
Description: VS.VSSTRESN where VS.VSTESTCD='HEIGHT' and VS.VISITNUM=1

Name: MT.ADSL.WEIGHTBL
Description: VS.VSSTRESN where VS.VSTESTCD='WEIGHT' and VS.VISITNUM=3

Name: MT.ADSL.EDUCLVL
Description: SC.SCSTRESN where SC.SCTESTCD="EDLEVEL"

Name: MT.ADSL.DISONDT
Description: MH.MHSTDTC where MH.MHCAT='PRIMARY DIAGNOSIS' converted to SAS date

Name: MT.ADSL.DURDIS
Description: number of months between Date of VISIT 1 and DISONDT

Name: MT.ADSL.DURDSGR1
Description: grouping DURDIS values as <12 and >=12

Name: MT.ADSL.VISIT1DT
Description: SV.SVSTDTC where SV.VISITNUM=1, converted to SAS date

Name: MT.ADSL.VISNUMEN
Description: If DS.VISITNUM=13 where DS.DSTERM='PROTOCOL COMPLETED' then VISNUMEN=12, otherwise VISNUMEN=DS.VISITNUM where DS.DSTERM='PROTOCOL COMPLETED'

Name: MT.ADSL.RFENDT
Description: RFENDTC converted to SAS date

Name: MT.ADSL.EOSSTT
Description: If DS.DSDECOD='COMPLETED' then EOSSTT='COMPLETED'. Otherwise EOSSTT='DISCONTINUED'.

Name: MT.ADSL.DCSREAS
Description: If DS.DSCAT='DISPOSITION EVENT' and DS.DSTERM in('I/E NOT MET' 'SPONSOR DECISION' 'WITHDREW CONSENT') then DCSREAS=DS.DSTERM. Otherwise if DS.DSCAT='DISPOSITION EVENT' then DCSREAS=DS.DSDECOD. Convert to mixed case to match display format.

Name: MT.ADSL.MMS1TSBL
Description: Sum of FT.FTSTRESN values where FT.FTCAT="MMSE" for the subject (FT.FTTESTCD= 'MMS101A'-'MMS111')

Name: MT.ADQSADAS.AVAL.ACTOT
Description: Sum of ADAS scores for items 1, 2, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 11, 12, 13, and 14, see ADRG for details on adjusting for missing values.

Name: MT.ADAE.ASTDT
Description: AE.AESTDTC, converted to a numeric SAS date. Some events with partial dates are imputed in a conservative manner. If the day component is missing, a value of '01' is used. If both the month and day are missing no imputation is performed as these dates clearly indicate a start prior to the beginning of treatment. There are no events with completely missing start dates.

Name: MT.ADAE.ASTDTF
Description: ASTDTF='D' if the day value within the character date is imputed. Note that only day values needed to be imputed for this study

Name: MT.ADAE.ASTDY
Description: IF ASTDT>=TRTSDT>MISSING then ASTDY=ASTDT-TRTSDT+1 Else if TRTSDT>ASTDT>MISSING then ASTDY=ASTDT-TRTSDT

Name: MT.ADAE.AENDT
Description: AE.AEENDTC, converted to a numeric SAS date

Name: MT.ADAE.AENDY
Description: IF AENDT>=TRTSDT>MISSING then AENDY=AENDT-TRTSDT+1 Else if TRTSDT>AENDT>MISSING then AENDY=AENDT-TRTSDT

Name: MT.ADAE.ADURN
Description: ADURN=AENDT-ASTDT+1

Name: MT.ADAE.ADURU
Description: If ADURN is not missing then ADURU='DAY'

Name: MT.ADAE.TRTEMFL
Description: If ASTDT >= TRTSDT > . then TRTEMFL='Y'. Otherwise TRTEMFL='N'

Name: MT.ADAE.AOCCFL
Description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCFL=’Y’) within each Subject

Name: MT.ADAE.AOCCSFL
Description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCSFL=’Y’) within each Subject and SOC

Name: MT.ADAE.AOCCPFL
Description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Preferred Term (AEDECOD), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCCPFL=’Y’) within each Subject, SOC, and PT

Name: MT.ADAE.AOCC02FL
Description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC02FL=’Y’) within each Subject

Name: MT.ADAE.AOCC03FL
Description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC03FL=’Y’) within each Subject and SOC

Name: MT.ADAE.AOCC04FL
Description: Subset to TRTEMFL='Y' and AESER='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), System Organ Class (AEBODSYS), Preferred Term (AEDECOD), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC04FL=’Y’) within each Subject, SOC, and PT

Name: MT.ADAE.CQ01NAM
Description: If AEDECOD contains any of the character strings of ('APPLICATION', 'DERMATITIS', 'ERYTHEMA', 'BLISTER') OR if AEBODSYS='SKIN AND SUBC UTANEOUS TISSUE DISORDERS' but AEDECOD is not in ('COLD SWEAT', 'HYPERHIDROSIS', 'ALOPECIA') then CQ01NAM='DERMATOLOGIC EVENTS' Otherwise CQ01NAM=NULL

Name: MT.ADAE.AOCC01FL
Description: Subset to CQ01NAM='' and TRTEMFL='Y' and sort by Subject (USUBJID), Start Date (ASTDT), and Sequence Number (AESEQ) and flag the first record (set AOCC01FL=’Y’) within each Subject (Flag First Treatment Emergent Dermatological Event for Time to Event Analysis)
